The management inﬂuence on carbon sequestration potential of different land use types are least known at the
national level. This research was conducted to assess the impact of area exclusion on carbon sequestration po-
tential in the two land use systems: protected natural vegetation (PNV) and communal grazing land (CGL). Data of
vegetation, litter, and soils were collected using systematic sampling methods, laying 19 transects and 62 quadrats
